favorites.content: Nothing in life is so exhilarating as to be shot at without result.
favorites.author: Winston Churchill

history.content: Men of perverse opinion do not know the excellence of what is in their hands, till someone dash it from them.
history.author: Sophocles

history.content: Most great people have attained their greatest success just one step beyond their greatest failure.
history.author: Napoleon Hill

history.content: If opportunity doesn't knock, build a door.
history.author: Milton Berle

history.content: Maxim for life: You get treated in life the way you teach people to treat you.
history.author: Wayne Dyer

history.content: The two most powerful warriors are patience and time.
history.author: Leo Tolstoy

history.content: Love all, trust a few, do wrong to none.
history.author: William Shakespeare

history.content: The greater our knowledge increases the more our ignorance unfolds.
history.author: John F. Kennedy

history.content: As you think, so shall you become.
history.author: Bruce Lee

quotes.content: Stay positive and happy. Work hard and don't give up hope.
quotes.author: Anonymous

quotes.content: Every day may not be good, but there is something good in every day.
quotes.author: Unknown

quotes.content: The only way to do great work is to love what you do.
quotes.author: Steve Jobs
